  "full_text": "An update for qemu-kvm is now available for Red Hat Enterprise Linux 10.\n\nKernel-based Virtual Machine (KVM) is a full virtualization solution for Linux on a variety of architectures. The qemu-kvm packages provide the user-space component for running virtual machines that use KVM.Bug Fix(es) and Enhancement(s): qemu-kvm: VNC WebSocket handshake use-after-free [rhel-9.7.z] (JIRA:RHEL-120125)  [rhel9] Backport \"arm/kvm: report registers we failed to set\" [rhel-9.7.z] (JIRA:RHEL-120502)"
